A closed loop view of data, across all touch points within an organisation, provides a single view of the customer.  Payment history, service challenges, marketing strategies that have provided value and details on tariffs can all be tracked using the Microsoft Dynamics CRM platform.  Regardless of the channels a customer uses to communicate, any CRM user can know the customer, transforming the customer experience.

¬If a customer has paid late for the last three quarters or if a particular address shows a pattern of late payments, (despite different tenants) it's reasonable to consider payments may continue to be late.¬Microsoft's analytics tools make it easy to identify these patterns and provide the insights to connect with customers to help with payment options or offer ways of reducing consumption.

Microsoft's powerful analytics and insights tools help to understand buying behaviours, preferences and what customers value the most.  Data is actionable, supporting decisions with tangible evidence.  With a better understanding of customers, experiences can be more personal and relevant, driving customer loyalty.

There is no longer one single way in which all customers want to interact with a supplier. To ensure customer loyalty and improve customer satisfaction it is important to offer relevant ways for customers to interact with your company. Increasingly this is driving towards mobile and social-based methods of communication and Microsoft can help with this transition.

With service differentiation and customer satisfaction increasingly hard to achieve, and even harder to maintain, the marketing, sales and service battle has refocused on customer experience - the experience an individual gets when they interact with the brand, its products & services, and its customer-facing people.
